208366622.comment:
>>208364509
For me it's Yuno. The best (not this pic) was that eyes only scene where she's in that deep trance working out where Reisuke hid his diary. That and her other prominent eye scenes almost make me think it was a reference to the 90s live action Hercules show since Yuno = Juno = Hera and Hera was portrayed in that show at least some of the time as just her eyes with peacock feathers in an effect that's hard to do justice through verbal description, you have to see it yourself to get it.
That said Juno / Hera was already known for having prominent eyes and being associated with the peacock and its many-eyed feathers in the original mythology long before TV even existed so it's just as likely the reference was to the original mythos and not to the live action Hercules show.
